.TH "alloc_pages_exact" 9 "alloc_pages_exact" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
alloc_pages_exact \- allocate an exact number physically-contiguous pages.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" alloc_pages_exact
.BI "(size_t size "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
the number of bytes to allocate
.IP "gfp_mask" 12
GFP flags for the allocation, must not contain __GFP_COMP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is similar to \fBalloc_pages\fP, except that it allocates the
minimum number of pages to satisfy the request.  \fBalloc_pages\fP can only
allocate memory in power-of-two pages.

This function is also limited by MAX_ORDER.

Memory allocated by this function must be released by \fBfree_pages_exact\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to the allocated area or NULL in case of error.
